                <note rend="inline" type="source">661.1115/101: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Denmark</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-17T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1920—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>69. Your 15, July 12, 4 p.m.</p>
                <p>Railway equipment is regarded as war material during duration of Bolshevik
                    hostilities. As all Americans will trade with Soviet Russia at their own risk
                    they must use Clearing House entirely at their own responsibility.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
